1601.definition: [ἐκπίπτω] from {{G1537}} and {{G4098}}; to drop away; specially, be driven out of one's course; figuratively, to lose, become inefficient

1602.definition: [ἐκπλέω] from {{G1537}} and {{G4126}}; to depart by ship

1605.definition: [ἐκπλήσσω] from {{G1537}} and {{G4141}}; to strike with astonishment

1607.definition: [ἐκπορεύομαι] from {{G1537}} and {{G4198}}; to depart, be discharged, proceed, project

1608.definition: [ἐκπορνεύω] from {{G1537}} and {{G4203}}; to be utterly unchaste

1609.definition: [ἐκπτύω] from {{G1537}} and {{G4429}}; to spit out, i.e. (figuratively) spurn

1611.definition: [ἔκστασις] from {{G1839}}; a displacement of the mind, i.e. bewilderment, "ecstasy"

1614.definition: [ἐκτείνω] from {{G1537}} and teino (to stretch); to extend

1617.definition: [ἐκτενέστερον] neuter of the comparative of {{G1618}}; more intently

1620.definition: [ἐκτίθημι] from {{G1537}} and {{G5087}}; to expose; figuratively, to declare

1621.definition: [ἐκτινάσσω] from {{G1537}} and tinasso (to swing); to shake violently

1622.definition: [ἐκτός] from {{G1537}}; the exterior; figuratively (as a preposition) aside from, besides

1624.definition: [ἐκτρέπω] from {{G1537}} and the base of {{G5157}}; to deflect, i.e. turn away (literally or figuratively)

1625.definition: [ἐκτρέφω] from {{G1537}} and {{G5142}}; to rear up to maturity, i.e. (genitive case) to cherish or train

1626.definition: [ἔκτρωμα] from a comparative of {{G1537}} and τιτρώσκω (to wound); a miscarriage (abortion), i.e. (by analogy) untimely birth

1627.definition: [ἐκφέρω] from {{G1537}} and {{G5342}}; to bear out (literally or figuratively)

1630.definition: [ἔκφοβος] from {{G1537}} and {{G5401}}; frightened out of one's wits

1632.definition: [ἐκχέω] ,     or (by variation)      ἐκχύνωfrom {{G1537}} and χέω (to pour); to pour forth; figuratively, to bestow

1636.definition: [ἐλαία] feminine of a presumed derivative from an obsolete primary; an olive (the tree or the fruit)

1637.definition: [ἔλαιον] neuter of the same as {{G1636}}; olive oil

1638.definition: [ἐλαιών] from {{G1636}}; an olive-orchard, i.e. (specially) the Mount of Olives

1639.definition: [Ἐλαμίτης] of Hebrew origin ({{H5867}}); an Elamite or Persian

1640.definition: [ἐλάσσων]   or ἐλάττωνcomparative of the same as {{G1646}}; smaller (in size, quantity, age or quality)

1641.definition: [ἐλαττονέω] from {{G1640}}; to diminish, i.e. fall short

1642.definition: [ἐλαττόω] from {{G1640}}; to lessen (in rank or influence)

1643.definition: [ἐλαύνω] a prolonged form of a primary verb (obsolete except in certain tenses as an alternative of this) of uncertain affinity; to push (as wind, oars or dæmonical power)

1645.definition: [ἐλαφρός] probably akin to {{G1643}} and the base of {{G1640}}; light, i.e. easy

1646.definition: [ἐλάχιστος] superlative of ἔλαχυς (short); used as equivalent to {{G3398}}; least (in size, amount, dignity, etc.)

1648.definition: [Ἐλεάζαρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H499}}); Eleazar, an Israelite

1651.definition: [ἐλέγχω] of uncertain affinity; to confute, admonish

1653.definition: [ἐλεέω] from {{G1656}}; to compassionate (by word or deed, specially, by divine grace)

1654.definition: [ἐλεημοσύνη] from {{G1656}}; compassionateness, i.e. (as exercised towards the poor) beneficence, or (concretely) a benefaction

1656.definition: [ἔλεος] of uncertain affinity; compassion (human or divine, especially active)

1657.definition: [ἐλευθερία] from {{G1658}}; freedom (legitimate or licentious, chiefly moral or ceremonial)

1658.definition: [ἐλεύθερος] probably from the alternate of {{G2064}}; unrestrained (to go at pleasure), i.e. (as a citizen) not a slave (whether freeborn or manumitted), or (genitive case) exempt (from obligation or liability)

1659.definition: [ἐλευθερόω] from {{G1658}}; to liberate, i.e. (figuratively) to exempt (from moral, ceremonial or mortal liability)

1660.definition: [ἔλευσις] from the alternate of {{G2064}}; an advent

1661.definition: [ἐλεφάντινος] from ἔλεφας (an "elephant"); elephantine, i.e. (by implication) composed of ivory

1662.definition: [Ἐλιακείμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H471}}); Eliakim, an Israelite

1663.definition: [Ἐλιέζερ] of Hebrew origin ({{H461}}); Eliezer, an Israelite

1664.definition: [Ἐλιούδ] of Hebrew origin ({{H410}} and {{H1935}}); God of majesty; Eliud, an Israelite

1665.definition: [Ἐλισάβετ] of Hebrew origin ({{H472}}); Elisabet, an Israelitess

1666.definition: [Ἐλισσαῖος] of Hebrew origin ({{H477}}); Elissæus, an Israelite

1667.definition: [ἑλίσσω] a form of {{G1507}}; to coil or wrap

1668.definition: [ἕλκος] probably from {{G1670}}; an ulcer (as if drawn together)

1669.definition: [ἑλκόω] from {{G1668}}; to cause to ulcerate, i.e. (passively) be ulcerous

1670.definition: [ἑλκύω]   or ἕλκω;  probably akin to {{G138}}; to drag (literally or figuratively) Compare {{G1667}}.

1671.definition: [Ἑλλάς] of uncertain affinity; Hellas (or Greece), a country of Europe

1672.definition: [Ἕλλην] from {{G1671}}; a Hellen (Grecian) or inhabitant of Hellas; by extension a Greek-speaking person, especially a non-Jew

1674.definition: [Ἑλληνίς] feminine of {{G1672}}; a Grecian (i.e. non-Jewish) woman

1675.definition: [Ἑλληνιστής] from a derivative of {{G1672}}; a Hellenist or Greek-speaking Jew

1676.definition: [Ἑλληνιστί] adverb from the same as {{G1675}}; Hellenistically, i.e. in the Grecian language

1677.definition: [ἐλλογέω] from {{G1722}} and {{G3056}} (in the sense of account); to reckon in, i.e. attribute

1678.definition: [Ἐλμωδάμ] of Hebrew origin (perhaps for {{H486}}); Elmodam, an Israelite

1680.definition: [ἐλπίς] from a primary ἔλπω (to anticipate, usually with pleasure); expectation (abstractly or concretely) or confidence

1681.definition: [Ἐλύμας] of foreign origin; Elymas, a wizard

1682.definition: [ἐλοΐ] of Chaldean origin ({{H426}} with pronominal suffix) my God

1683.definition: [ἐμαυτοῦ] genitive case compound of {{G1700}} and {{G846}}; of myself so likewise the dative case      ἐμαυτῷ, and accusative case      ἐμαυτόν

1684.definition: [ἐμβαίνω] from {{G1722}} and the base of {{G939}}; to walk on, i.e. embark (aboard a vessel), reach (a pool)

1685.definition: [ἐμβάλλω] from {{G1722}} and {{G906}}; to throw on, i.e. (figuratively) subject to (eternal punishment)

1686.definition: [ἐμβάπτω] from {{G1722}} and {{G911}}; to whelm on, i.e. wet (a part of the person, etc.) by contact with a fluid

1687.definition: [ἐμβατεύω] from {{G1722}} and a presumed derivative of the base of {{G939}}; equivalent to {{G1684}}; to intrude on (figuratively)

1688.definition: [ἐμβιβάζω] from {{G1722}} and βιβάζω (to mount; causative of {{G1684}}); to place on, i.e. transfer (aboard a vessel)

1689.definition: [ἐμβλέπω] from {{G1722}} and {{G991}}; to look on, i.e. (relatively) to observe fixedly, or (absolutely) to discern clearly

1690.definition: [ἐμβριμάομαι] from {{G1722}} and βριμάομαι (to snort with anger); to have indignation on, i.e. (transitively) to blame, (intransitively) to sigh with chagrin, (specially) to sternly enjoin

1693.definition: [ἐμμαίνομαι] from {{G1722}} and {{G3105}}; to rave on, i.e. rage at

1694.definition: [Ἐμμανουήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{H6005}}); God with us; Emmanuel, a name of Christ

1695.definition: [Ἐμμαούς] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{H3222}}); Emmaus, a place in Palestine

1696.definition: [ἐμμένω] from {{G1722}} and {{G3306}}; to stay in the same place, i.e. (figuratively) persevere

1697.definition: [Ἐμμόρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H2544}}); Emmor (i.e. Chamor), a Canaanite

1698.definition: [ἐμοί] a prolonged form of {{G3427}}; to me

1699.definition: [ἐμός] from the oblique cases of {{G1473}} ({{G1698}}, {{G1700}}, {{G1691}}); my

1700.definition: [ἐμοῦ] a prolonged form of {{G3449}}; of me
